g2:c.BORDERLESS-FREE-TEXT.g2:a.TEXT: This tests drawing, and printing. It works by drawing a series of workspaces at various scales. It then prints them. It invokes a mechanism to convert them into bitmaps and then into a checksum. It checks that checksum against a stored value. Each test has a subworkspace and these are what we print. Workspaces have a "draw-test-manager" object on them to configure the printer, and record the checksum. NOTE: -- This test does not pass in ab-sep92, it should pass in ab.

g2:c.PROCEDURE.g2:a.TEXT: win32-print(test-name: symbol, wks: class kb-workspace) = (item-or-value) begin return the symbol unavailable; end
